SUMMARY:Birding Tour at Hart-Miller Island on May 14\, 2026
DESCRIPTION:Feast your eyes on some of the most extraordinary birds that Maryland has to offer.  \nThe Maryland Port Administration is pleased to welcome the general public to participate in an upcoming birding tour. This birding experience is free to the public. \nPlease note the Birding Tour Details and Safety Information below before registering. Questions can be directed to the birding tour leader at Maryland Ports Birding [birdingtours@menv.com]. \nLottery Entrance Deadline: May 3\, at 11:59 pm\nLottery Selections Announced: May 4\, 2026\nEvent Date: May 14\, 2026 (if selected\, please arrive by 8:45am)\nEvent Location 2024A Riverview Road\, Essex\, MD 21221 Parking: Take a right into the lot\, and park in the gravel area. Please wait by the shed until an MES staff member meets you. \nRegistration for this event has closed. \n\n\nTour Details & Safety Information for Confirmed Registrants\nBirding tours are typically held on unpaved roads with rock\, gravel\, or mud with the potential of crossing shallow water. This walk may traverse several miles of uneven terrain. We recommend bringing telescopes\, binoculars\, water\, and adequate sun protection. Please wear sturdy\, closed-toe shoes (i.e.\, no sandals or thin-soled sneakers). \nThe birding tour may be canceled in the event of high winds or inclement weather. Please check your email 24 hours before the event to be sure there has been no unforeseen cancellation. This walk may be canceled on the morning of the event due to unforeseen circumstances.  \nOur birding tours are popular and often have a waitlist. If you need to cancel\, please notify us immediately by emailing Maryland Ports Birding [birdingtours@menv.com]\, so your spot can be allocated to someone on the waitlist. \n\n 
URL:https://maryland-dmmp.com/event/birding-tour-at-hart-miller-island-on-may-14-2026/
LOCATION:Hart-Miller Island\, 2024A Riverview Rd\, Essex\, MD\, 21221\, United States
CATEGORIES:Birding Tours
END:VEVENT
